WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.920
[Amit Varma]: As we grow up, we believe that by and large, we should not interfere with other people's

00:00:08.920 --> 00:00:09.920
[Amit Varma]: business.

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:14.720
[Amit Varma]: And it seems natural to transplant this thinking from individuals to countries.

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:17.680
[Amit Varma]: We should not interfere with another country's internal affairs.

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:22.480
[Amit Varma]: After all, we don't like it if other countries interfere with our own internal affairs.

00:00:22.480 --> 00:00:23.480
[Amit Varma]: Right?

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.060
[Amit Varma]: Well, what if it's not quite that simple?

00:00:26.060 --> 00:00:28.520
[Amit Varma]: What if countries are not like people?

00:00:28.520 --> 00:00:34.620
[Amit Varma]: What if geopolitics, unlike trade between individuals, is often a zero-sum game?

00:00:34.620 --> 00:00:37.300
[Amit Varma]: What should we do about Maldives?

